WestLB’s Bad Bank Reports First-Half Loss on Greek Writedowns

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-08-11T13:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/westlb-s-bad-bank-reports-first-half-loss-on-greek-writedowns.html
 WestLB AG’s bad bank, Erste
Abwicklungsanstalt, reported a loss in the first half of the
year after writing down the value of its Greek holdings by 21
percent.  EAA reported a loss of 176 million euros ($249 million) in
the six months through June, including 243 million euros in
writedowns, the Dusseldorf, Germany-based company said in an e-
mailed statement today.  EAA reduced its total balance sheet by 7.2 billion euros
in the first seven months of 2011 to 56.5 billion euros,
compared with an original transfer value of 77.5 billion euros,
it added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
